php-express
============================

POST and Binary transport are supported

Currently useful for rapid testing your php apps. 
But about 3-4 times slower than a normal nginx installation. 



    var express = require("express");

    var app = express.createServer();

    var options = {
	    host: "127.0.0.1",
	    port: "9000",
	    root: __dirname + "/",
	    server: {
		    host: "127.0.0.1",
		    port: 3005
	    }
    };

    var agent = new php.Agent(4, options);

    app.use(function (req, res, next) {
	    var url = urlp.parse(req.url);
	    var ext = path.extname(url.pathname);
	    if(ext === ".php") {
            agent.request(req,res,next);

	    }else{
            res.end()
	    }
    }).listen(options.server.port, options.server.host);



##dependencies
* express
* running php-fpm server (same thing you would install if nginx is used)




